      "page_index": 0,
      "raw_text": "February 2002\nHigh-pressure hoselines\nDimensions in mm\nApplication\nThe hoses are used in high-pressure hydraulic systems operating on mineral-oil basis or with water-glycol emulsions and for\nlight fuel oils, lubricating oils, air and water.\nThese hoselines are comparable and interchangeable with the corresponding types of AEROQUIP and ARGUS and\ntherefore should be used with preference.\nSpecification in the bill of materials:\nComplete hoselines are specified in the bill of materials on AP (order item) level. This means that the components\n(hose and fittings) are specified only by the operations scheduling department on AUP (order sub-item) level.\nHoselines with fire protection (thermal protection) are specified as bought-out item numbers with indication of the\nthermal stability.\nShape A\nShape B\n(from DN 6 - DN 32)\n(from DN 6 - DN 8)\nfor welding cone couplings\nfor solderless pipe couplings\nShape C - E\n(from DN 12 - DN 32)\nfor SAE flange connection 6000 psi\nDesignation of a complete high-pressure hoseline (4SH), shape A, nominal width of DN 25 and length 1000 mm:\nHoseline SN 756 – 4SA 25 x 1000\nOperat. Pressure\nbar\nWeight\nkg/m\nDN\nd1\nd2\nd3\n2)\nd4\n3)\nd5\nd6\n4)\nl3\nBending\nRadius\nrmin\ns\ndynamic\nstatic\nA\nB\nC - E\n6\n-\n20\n0,45\n-\n8\n-\n22\n0,45\n-\nH\n6\n6,4\n15,0\n10\nM18 x 1,5\n22\n-\n26\n100\n22\n600\n0,53\n0,47\n-\nH\n8\n7,9\n16,6\n12\nM20 x 1,5\n24\n-\n26\n115\n24\n350\n560\n0,60\n0,54\n-\n(H)\n(12)\n12,7\n22,2\n-\nM24 x 1,5\n30\n-\n-\n180\n30\n275\n440\n0,93\n-\n-\n(H)\n(16)\n15,9\n25,4\n-\nM30 x 2\n33\n-\n-\n36\n1,29\n-\n-\n(H)\n(20)\n19,0\n29,3\n-\nM36 x 2\n38\n-\n-\n240\n46\n215\n340\n1,82\n-\n-\n4H\n12\n12,7\n24,6\n-\nM24 x 1,5\n30\n31,7\n-\n230\n30\n415\n660\n1,19\n-\n1,29\n4H\n16\n15,9\n28,2\n-\nM30 x 2\n33\n31,7\n-\n36\n350\n1,69\n-\n1,77\n4H\n20\n19,0\n32,2\n-\nM36 x 2\n38\n41,3\n-\n300\n46\n350\n2,37\n-\n2,31\n(H)\n(25)\n25,4\n39,7\n-\nM42 x 2\n46\n47,6\n-\n340\n50\n280\n3,35\n-\n2,92\n(H)\n(32)\n31,8\n50,8\n-\nM52 x 2\n58\n54,0\n-\n460\n60\n210\n300\n5,25\n-\n4,45\n4SH\n25\n25,4\n38,7\n-\nM42 x 2\n46\n47,6\n-\n340\n50\n380\n550\n3,38\n-\n3,08\n4SH\n32\n31,8\n45,5\n-\nM52 x 2\n56\n63,5\n-\n460\n60\n350\n4,74\n-\n4,14\nIf possbile, do not use nominal widths shown in round brackets.\nThe static oerating pressure must only be used with highly aqueous power fluids which are predominantly subject to static\nloads.\nFootnotes see page 2\nContinued on page 2\nBearbeitet: Normung\n18.07.01\nShape D\nShape E\nNo guarantee can be given in respect of this translation\nIn all cases the latest German-language version\nof this standard shall be taken as authoritative\nThis copy will not be updated in case of changes!",
