    {
      "page_index": 1,
      "raw_text": "SN 756 : 2002-01\nStandard lengths for hoseline\n160\n315\n630\n800\n1000\n1250\n1400\n1600\n1800\n2000\n2500\n3150\n4000\nAdmissible length deviation\nl1\nup to 630\nover 630\nto 1250\nover 1250\nto 2500\nover 2500\nto 8000\nover 8000\n≤ DN25\n+ 7\n- 3\n+12\n- 4\n+20\n- 6\nDN32\n+12\n- 4\n+20\n- 6\n+25\n- 6\n+ 1,5%\n- 0,5%\n+ 3%\n- 1%\nThe angular position for hoselines with two-side elbow fittings (shapes D + E) can be determined as follows.\nLook along the hoseline with the rear fitting (the one pointing away from\nyou) pointing to top.\nThen specify the degree at which the front fitting is turned in clockwise di-\nrection.\nE.g. turned by 140° (this specification is to be indicated in the bill of mate-\nrial) Tolerance ± 3°.\nHoseline SN 756 – 4SHDE 32 x 800 – turned by 140°\nFor low pressure hoselines, please refer to SN 544\n1) Specification of length as required for the purpose, but the standard lengths are to be taken into account.\n2) For solderless pipe couplings with cutting ring, please refer to SN 456.\n3) For male studs and weld-on sockets, please refer to SN 759.\n4) For SAE flanges, please refer to SN 532.",
